The scripts build a GCC that runs on this platform that produces
binaries for another platform (it's a cross compiler).
Then, the cross-GCC builds Linux.

Primary documentation

Scripts and steps:
https://www.linuxjournal.com/content/diy-build-custom-minimal-linux-distribution-source

Which package versions to use:
http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/lfs/downloads/9.0/LFS-BOOK-9.0-NOCHUNKS.html#pre-hostreqs
